Even a second child plan failed because of the abortion ban

In the spring of this year, the Deputy Minister of Health Oksana Shulyar enumerated the main problems women face. According to her, less than 36% of women are satisfied with the length of the waiting period for contraception at a gynecological appointment. Only 83% of respondents had a clinical test, which is far from the proportion of women.

In addition, the psychologist is worried that, despite numerous statements from the Ministry of Health, many women still do not undergo regular clinical tests because of their conduct, including the implementation of “mini courses” of contraception. As the survey shows, nearly 1/3 of permissible attempts are made by means of emergency contraceptive pills or unprotected sex, after emergency abstention, and almost 19% of women take two means of emergency contraception.

A quarter of the women also confirmed that they did not message their doctor beforehand about having sex after withdrawal of attempts. However, others were willing to recommend to their girlfriends the success of such attempts and for some it is an effective way to combat contraception.
